goals.rationale: This helps in understanding the average number of persons associated with each group and if there is any significant difference in the number of persons across different groups.

goals.rationale: This helps in understanding the proportion of each group ID in the dataset.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='group', data=data)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of persons across different groups?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    names = ' '.join(data['person'].tolist())
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=480, height=480, margin=0).generate(names)
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.title("What is the most common name among all persons in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    group_counts = data.groupby('group')['person'].count().reset_index()
    group_counts['average_count'] = group_counts['person'] / group_counts['group'].nunique()
    
    sns.lineplot(x='group', y='average_count', data=group_counts)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the average number of persons associated with each group?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(group_counts, labels=group_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group IDs in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    sns.histplot(data=data, x='name_length', bins=20)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the length of person names in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;
